1
00:00:03,212 --> 00:00:05,589
The Tardis is still in the same place
but the Earth has gone.

2
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:07,216
Exterminate!

3
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:15,432
Welcome to my new empire.

4
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:18,060
Ladies and gentlemen, we are at war.

5
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:20,479
Exterminate Torchwood!

6
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:29,947
I surrender! I'm sorry!

7
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:32,157
The Doctor is coming!

8
00:00:34,493 --> 00:00:36,495
He's dying, and you know
what happens next.

9
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:39,206
-But he can't.
-What do you mean? What happens next?

10
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:41,208
I'm regenerating.

11
00:00:43,085 --> 00:00:45,337
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

12
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:34,344
Ah!

13
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:36,930
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

14
00:01:39,975 --> 00:01:42,352
Now then, where were we?

15
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,065
-Exterminate!
-Exterminate!

16
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:56,825
-Mickey?
-Us Smiths gotta stick together.

17
00:01:57,534 --> 00:02:01,204
Jackie Tyler. Rose's mum.
Now, where the hell is my daughter?

18
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:33,862
What the hell?

19
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,698
There now.

20
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,162
You see?

21
00:02:42,788 --> 00:02:44,831
Used the regeneration energy
to heal myself,

22
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:46,625
but as soon as that was done,
I didn't need to change.

23
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,502
I didn't want to, why would I?
Look at me.

24
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:50,545
So to stop the energy going all the way,

25
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:53,173
I siphoned off the rest into
a handy bio-matching receptacle,

26
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:57,260
namely, my hand, my hand there.
My handy spare hand!

27
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:59,346
Remember? Christmas Day, Sycorax?

28
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:02,557
Lost my hand in a sword fight?
That's my hand!

29
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:04,351
What do you think?

30
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:11,274
You're still you?

31
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:14,111
I'm still me.

32
00:03:21,118 --> 00:03:23,036
You can hug me if you want.

33
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:25,956
No, really, you can hug me.

34
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,463
IANTO: It's a time lock.

35
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:36,007
The ultimate defence programme.
Tosh was working on it.

36
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:39,177
I never thought she finished it,
but she did!

37
00:03:39,261 --> 00:03:42,848
The Hub's sealed in a time bubble,
nothing can get in.

38
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,850
-But that means we can get out.
-Nope.

39
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,227
Not without unlocking that Dalek.

40
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:50,230
We're trapped inside.
It's all up to Jack now.

41
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:53,400
DALEK: Report! Tardis has been located.

42
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:55,152
DALEK SUPREME: Bring it here!

43
00:03:55,277 --> 00:04:00,615
Bring the Doctor to me!
Initiate temporal prison!

44
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:06,455
DALEX. Temporal prison initiated!

45
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:13,503
DOCTOR: They've got us! Power's gone!

46
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:17,340
Some kind of chronon loop.

47
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:22,846
DALEX:. Transferring Tardis
to the crucible.

48
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:33,440
Those teleport things, can we use them?

49
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:35,233
If they've taken the Doctor
to the Dalek spaceship,

50
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:37,360
then that's where we need to be.

51
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:39,738
It's not just a teleport,
it's a Dimension Jump.

52
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,865
This thing rips a hole
in the fabric of space.

53
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,116
SARAH JANE: But can we use it?

54
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,911
Not yet, it burns up energy.
Needs half an hour between jumps.

55
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:48,246
-Then put down your guns.
-Do what?

56
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:51,374
If you're carrying a gun,
they'll shoot you dead.

57
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:56,963
Daleks! I surrender!

58
00:04:57,047 --> 00:05:01,885
DALEK: All humans in this sector
will be taken to the crucible!

59
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:03,178
She's bloody mad!

60
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:07,516
Yeah, but, Mickey, if they've got
the Doctor then they've got Rose.

61
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,520
And us. We surrender.

62
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:20,153
Now Jack's explained the base code,
I know how this teleport works.

63
00:05:20,237 --> 00:05:23,698
I think. But you just stay indoors,
there's no Daleks on this street,

64
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:25,909
you should be all right,
just keep quiet.

65
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,577
But where are you going?

66
00:05:27,661 --> 00:05:30,831
I'm a member of UNIT. And
they gave me the Osterhagen Key.

67
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:34,084
I've got to do my job. I'm sorry.

68
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:37,504
Martha, what's an Osterhagen Key?

69
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:41,258
Tell me. What does it do?

70
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:43,093
Love you.

71
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,938
(DALEKS SPEAKING GERMAN)

72
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:14,666
JACK: There's a massive Dalek ship
at the centre of the planets.

73
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:18,628
They're calling it the Crucible.
Guess that's our destination.

74
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:21,715
You said these planets
were like an engine. But what for?

75
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,675
Rose? You've been in a parallel world,

76
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,510
that world's running ahead
of this universe.

77
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:28,054
You've seen the future. What was it?

78
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:32,142
-It's the darkness.
-The stars were going out.

79
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:36,563
One by one. We looked up
at the sky and they were just dying.

80
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:40,817
Basically, we've been building
this travel machine,

81
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:44,654
this... This Dimension Cannon
so I could...

82
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,741
Well, so I could...

83
00:06:47,824 --> 00:06:49,951
-What?
-So I could come back.

84
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:56,374
Shut up. Anyway, suddenly
it started to work

85
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,335
and the dimensions started to collapse.

86
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:01,379
Not just in our world, not just
in yours, but the whole of reality.

87
00:07:01,463 --> 00:07:04,966
Even the Void was dead.
Something is destroying everything.

88
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:09,262
In that parallel world,
you said something about me.

89
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:12,807
The Dimension Cannon could
measure time lines and it's...

90
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:16,019
It's weird, Donna, but they
all seem to converge on you.

91
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:19,940
But why me?
I mean, what have I ever done?

92
00:07:20,023 --> 00:07:23,151
I'm a temp from Chiswick!

93
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,653
(BEEPING)

94
00:07:25,195 --> 00:07:28,365
The Dalek Crucible. All aboard!

95
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:47,384
DALEX. The Tardis is secured.

96
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:54,391
Doctor, you will step forth or die.

97
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:59,521
We'll have to go out.
'Cause if we don't, they'll get in.

98
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:02,649
You told me nothing could
get through those doors.

99
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,985
You've got extrapolator shielding.

100
00:08:05,068 --> 00:08:06,736
Last time we fought the Daleks,

101
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:09,698
they were scavengers
and hybrids and mad.

102
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:13,743
But this is a fully-fledged Dalek Empire
at the height of its power,

103
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:17,831
experts at fighting Tardises,
they can do anything.

104
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:22,210
Right now, that wooden door
is just wood.

105
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,461
(HEART BEATING)

106
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:25,255
JACK: What about your Dimension Jump?

107
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:27,757
ROSE: It needs another 20 minutes.
And anyway, I'm not leaving.

108
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:30,760
DOCTOR: What about your teleport?
JACK: Went down with the power loss.

109
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,595
DOCTOR: Right then,

110
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,639
all of us together. Yeah.

111
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:37,767
Donna?

112
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:43,023
Donna.

113
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:44,774
Yeah.

114
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:47,027
I'm sorry,
there's nothing else we can do.

115
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:48,653
I know.

116
00:08:50,739 --> 00:08:55,035
Surrender, Doctor,
and face your Dalek masters.

117
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:58,079
DALEK: Crucible on maximum alert!

118
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:00,040
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY) Daleks!

119
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:01,916
Oh, God!

120
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:06,504
It's been good, though, hasn't it?

121
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:10,508
All of us, all of it. Everything we did.

122
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,095
You were brilliant.

123
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:17,515
And you were brilliant.

124
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:21,019
And you were brilliant.

125
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:24,230
Blimey.

126
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:42,832
DALEK: Daleks reign supreme.
All hail the Daleks!

127
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:45,543
ALL: Daleks reign supreme.
All hail the Daleks!

128
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:47,754
(HEART BEATING)

129
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:51,091
Daleks reign supreme.
All hail the Daleks!

130
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:55,470
Daleks reign supreme.
All hail the Daleks!

131
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:57,847
SUPREME DALEK: Behold, Doctor!

132
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:02,185
Behold the might of the true Dalek race!

133
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,271
(HEART BEATING)

134
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:10,360
Donna! You're no safer in there.

135
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:15,824
Donna?

136
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:17,158
Doctor?

137
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:20,245
-What have you done?
-It wasn't me, I didn't do anything!

138
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,123
Oi! Oi, I'm not staying behind!

139
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:27,085
-What did you do?
-This is not of Dalek origin.

140
00:10:28,378 --> 00:10:29,587
Doctor!

141
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:33,049
Stop it, she's my friend.
Now, open the door and let her out.

142
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:37,512
-This is Time Lord treachery.
-Hey, the door just closed on its own!

143
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:41,641
Nevertheless, the Tardis is a weapon.

144
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:44,519
And it will be destroyed!

145
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:52,569
What are you doing? Bring it back!

146
00:10:55,864 --> 00:10:58,741
-Doctor!
-What've you done? Where's it going?

147
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:03,454
The Crucible has a heart of
Z-Neutrino energy.

148
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:08,126
The Tardis will be deposited
into the core.

149
00:11:08,293 --> 00:11:11,004
You can't.
You've taken the defences down.

150
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:12,463
It'll be torn apart!

151
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,484
-But Donna's still in there!
-Let her go!

152
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:41,117
The female and the Tardis
will perish together. Observe!

153
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:47,665
The last child of Gallifrey
ls powerless.

154
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:56,799
Please, I'm begging you,
I'll do anything!

155
00:11:56,925 --> 00:11:58,301
Put me in her place.

156
00:11:58,384 --> 00:12:01,471
You can do anything to me, I don't care,
just get her out of there!

157
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,853
(HEART BEATING)

158
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:36,923
You are connected to the Tardis.

159
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:39,509
Now feel it die!

160
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,126
-It's you.
-Oh, yes!

161
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:18,381
-You're naked.
-Oh, yes!

162
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:24,304
DALEX:. Total Tardis destruction
in 10 rels.

163
00:13:24,387 --> 00:13:27,640
Nine, eight, seven,

164
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,143
six, five,

165
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:34,731
four, three two, one.

166
00:13:34,856 --> 00:13:38,109
The Tardis has been destroyed.

167
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,737
Now, tell me, Doctor,

168
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:43,906
what do you feel?

169
00:13:44,282 --> 00:13:47,368
Anger? Sorrow?

170
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,246
Despair?

171
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,999
Yeah.

172
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:56,586
Then if emotions are so important,

173
00:13:56,711 --> 00:13:59,922
surely we have enhanced you?

174
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,549
Yeah? Feel this!

175
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:04,886
Exterminate!

176
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:14,187
Jack! Oh, my God! Oh, no...

177
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:18,941
-Rose, come here, leave him.
-They killed him.

178
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:22,070
I know. I'm sorry.

179
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:25,948
-Escort them to the Vault.
-There's nothing we can do.

180
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:29,786
They are the playthings of Davros now.

181
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:43,466
All repaired. Lovely. Shh!

182
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:45,259
No one knows we're here.
Gotta keep quiet.

183
00:14:45,343 --> 00:14:47,887
Silent running, like on submarines
when they can't even drop a spanner.

184
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,722
Don't drop a spanner. I like blue.
What do you think?

185
00:14:49,806 --> 00:14:51,974
You are bonkers.

186
00:14:52,058 --> 00:14:54,394
-Why, what's wrong with blue?
-Is that what Time Lords do?

187
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,354
Lop a bit off, grow another one?
You're like worms!

188
00:14:56,479 --> 00:14:59,816
No, no, no, no, no. I'm unique.
Never been another like me.

189
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,026
'Cause all that regeneration energy
went into the hand.

190
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:05,071
Look at my hand! I love that hand!
But then you touched it, wham!

191
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:06,656
Shh!

192
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:09,534
Instantaneous biological met a crisis.

193
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:13,246
I grew out of you.
Still, could be worse.

194
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:16,707
-0i! Watch it, spaceman!
-0i! Watch it, Earth girl! Ooh.

195
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:22,630
I sound like you.
I sound all... All sort of rough.

196
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:23,923
-Oi!
-0i!

197
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:25,550
-Oi!
-Spanners! Shh!

198
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:29,178
I must've picked up a bit of your voice,
that's all. Is it? Did I? No!

199
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:33,307
Ooh, you are kidding me! No way!

200
00:15:33,516 --> 00:15:36,602
One heart. I've got one heart!

201
00:15:37,145 --> 00:15:39,814
This body has got only one heart!

202
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:45,987
-Like you're human?
-Oh, that's disgusting.

203
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:47,155
-Oi!
-0i!

204
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:48,406
Stop it!

205
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:53,077
No, wait, I'm part Time Lord,
part human.

206
00:15:55,538 --> 00:15:57,373
Well, isn't that wizard?

207
00:15:57,498 --> 00:16:00,543
I kept hearing that noise,
that heartbeat.

208
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:02,879
Oh, that was me. My single heart.

209
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,547
I'm a complicated event
in time and space,

210
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,425
it must have rippled back,
converging on you.

211
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,218
But why me?

212
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:12,597
-'Cause you're special.
-I keep telling you, I'm not!

213
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:14,974
No, but you are.

214
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:20,897
Oh, you really don't believe that,
do you?

215
00:16:22,732 --> 00:16:25,902
I can see, Donna, what you're thinking.

216
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:29,655
All that attitude, all that lip,
"cause all this time

217
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:33,451
-you think you're not worth it.
-Stop it.

218
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:35,661
Shouting at the world
"cause no one's listening.

219
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:39,290
-Well, why should they?
-Doctor, stop it.

220
00:16:39,749 --> 00:16:42,043
But look at what you did.

221
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:45,296
No, it's more than that, it's like

222
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:49,675
we were always heading for this.

223
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:54,222
You came to the Tardis.

224
00:16:54,305 --> 00:16:57,350
Then you found me again.
Your granddad! Your car.

225
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,478
Donna, your car. You parked your car

226
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:03,231
right where the Tardis was
going to land, that's not coincidence.

227
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:04,649
Oh, we've been blind.

228
00:17:04,774 --> 00:17:06,901
Something's been drawing us together
for such a long time.

229
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:12,573
But you're talking like destiny.
There's no such thing, is there?

230
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:17,203
It's still not finished.
Like the pattern's not complete,

231
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:21,249
the strands are still drawing together.
But heading for what?

232
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:30,007
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

233
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:42,853
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

234
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:46,399
(WITH GERMAN ACCENT)
That accent, that is London, ja?

235
00:17:46,691 --> 00:17:48,859
I went to London. Long time ago.

236
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:50,861
I thought this place
was supposed to be guarded.

237
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:53,406
They were soldiers. Boys.

238
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,408
I brought them food, every day.

239
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:59,453
But when the Albtraume came
from the sky, they went home, to die.

240
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:02,623
-But not you?
-I've got a job to do.

241
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:31,152
London, in those days, to see it!

242
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:34,363
So much glamour. I was so young.

243
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:39,660
I heard the soldiers talking.
Many times.

244
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:43,247
They would speak of the Osterhagen Key.

245
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:48,461
I think London must be changed now, yes?

246
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,421
But still, the glamour.

247
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:53,257
(GUN CLICKING)

248
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,886
You will not go.

249
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:59,138
I've got no choice.

250
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:02,391
I know the Key. What it does.

251
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,937
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

252
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:16,447
Then do it.

253
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:28,334
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

254
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:32,755
I know.

255
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:37,468
Commence disposal. Incinerate!

256
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:46,102
Disposal completed.

257
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:21,137
This is Osterhagen Station One.

258
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:24,140
My name is Martha Jones.
Is there anyone there? Over.

259
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:29,895
DALEK: Prisoners now
on board the Crucible.

260
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:32,648
They will be taken for testing!

261
00:20:33,149 --> 00:20:35,317
One step closer to the Doctor.

262
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:43,284
Activate the holding cells.

263
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:48,122
Excellent.

264
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:53,252
Even when powerless,
a Time Lord is best contained.

265
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:55,296
Still scared of me, then?

266
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:59,967
It is time we talked, Doctor,
after so very long.

267
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:02,136
No, no, no, we're not doing
the nostalgia tour.

268
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:04,180
I want to know what's happening
right here, right now.

269
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:07,099
'Cause the Supreme Dalek
said Vault, yeah?

270
00:21:07,183 --> 00:21:10,895
As in dungeon. Cellar. Prison.

271
00:21:11,395 --> 00:21:13,689
You're not in charge of
the Daleks, are you?

272
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:18,068
They've got you locked away down here in
the basement like, what, a servant?

273
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:20,905
A slave? Court jester?

274
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:24,408
We have...an arrangement.

275
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:29,830
No, no, no, no, no. I've got the word.
You're the Dalek's pet.

276
00:21:29,914 --> 00:21:33,709
So very full of fire, is he not?

277
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:37,546
And to think you crossed
entire universes,

278
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:41,634
striding parallel to parallel
to find him again.

279
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:45,763
-Leave her alone.
-She is mine, to do as I please.

280
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:47,473
Then why am I still alive?

281
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:51,393
You must be here. It was foretold.

282
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:55,314
Even the Supreme Dalek
would not dare to contradict

283
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:57,608
the prophecies of Dalek Caan.

284
00:21:58,818 --> 00:22:03,989
DALEK CAAN: So cold and dark,
fire is coming,

285
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:07,034
the endless flames.

286
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:08,828
What is that thing?

287
00:22:08,911 --> 00:22:12,706
You've met before.
The last of the Cult of Skaro.

288
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:17,086
But it flew into the Time War,
unprotected.

289
00:22:17,211 --> 00:22:22,341
Caan did more than that he saw Time.

290
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:27,596
Its infinite complexity and
majesty raging through his mind.

291
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:31,767
And he saw you. Both of you.

292
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:36,105
This I have foreseen
in the wild, in the wind.

293
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:39,775
The Doctor will be here as witness

294
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,194
at the end of everything.

295
00:22:42,278 --> 00:22:45,823
The Doctor and his precious
children of time.

296
00:22:45,990 --> 00:22:47,825
(EVIL LAUGH)

297
00:22:48,158 --> 00:22:50,828
And one of them will die!

298
00:22:51,245 --> 00:22:53,747
Was it you, Caan? Did you kill Donna?

299
00:22:53,831 --> 00:22:56,083
Why did the Tardis door close? Tell me!

300
00:22:56,166 --> 00:23:00,754
Oh, that's it! The anger! The fire!

301
00:23:00,838 --> 00:23:05,968
The rage of a Time Lord
who butchered millions.

302
00:23:06,927 --> 00:23:08,470
There he is.

303
00:23:11,056 --> 00:23:12,558
Why so shy?

304
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:16,645
Show your companion.
Show her your true self.

305
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:20,691
Dalek Caan has promised me that, too.

306
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:24,361
I have seen at the time of ending

307
00:23:24,445 --> 00:23:28,365
the Doctor's soul will be revealed.

308
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,700
What does that mean?

309
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:32,328
We will discover it together.

310
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:34,330
Our final journey.

311
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:40,127
Because the ending approaches,
the testing begins.

312
00:23:40,294 --> 00:23:41,837
Testing of what?

313
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:46,300
The Reality Bomb.

314
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:54,516
DALEK: Prisoners will stand in
the designated area!

315
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,186
Move! Move!

316
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:06,612
You will stand!

317
00:24:07,363 --> 00:24:10,449
-I can't.
-You will stand!

318
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:12,534
I can't. Please.

319
00:24:12,618 --> 00:24:14,995
On your feet. On your feet!

320
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:17,498
Mickey, Mickey.

321
00:24:18,374 --> 00:24:19,792
Jackie.

322
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:23,504
Prisoners will stand
in the designated area!

323
00:24:23,587 --> 00:24:26,590
-We can't just leave her!
-No, Mickey, wait!

324
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:30,219
...in 30 rels.

325
00:24:30,344 --> 00:24:32,179
What does it mean?
What are they testing?

326
00:24:32,262 --> 00:24:34,014
What are they gonna do?

327
00:24:37,851 --> 00:24:40,437
I reckon it's that thing there.

328
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:44,066
SUPREME DALEK:
Testing calibration of Reality Bomb.

329
00:24:44,191 --> 00:24:46,902
Firing in 10 rels.

330
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:50,280
Nine, eight, seven, six...

331
00:24:50,406 --> 00:24:55,077
Behold the apotheosis of my genius!

332
00:24:56,787 --> 00:24:58,914
...one, Zero.

333
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:01,959
Activate planetary alignment field!

334
00:25:06,422 --> 00:25:09,591
It's the planets. The 27 planets!

335
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:21,770
But that's Z-Neutrino energy.

336
00:25:21,979 --> 00:25:24,606
Flattened by the alignment of
the planets into a single string.

337
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:27,443
No! Davros! Davros, you can't!

338
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:29,528
You can't! No!

339
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,281
Single string Z-Neutrinos
compressed into...

340
00:25:34,992 --> 00:25:37,453
No. No way!

341
00:25:57,639 --> 00:25:59,475
(BEEPING)

342
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:03,395
Thirty minutes. It's recharged!

343
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:06,315
(INAUDIBLE)

344
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:09,151
Use it!

345
00:26:14,656 --> 00:26:16,241
I'm so sorry.

346
00:26:47,523 --> 00:26:49,691
Test completed.

347
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:51,568
What was it?

348
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:56,240
Doctor, what did it do?

349
00:26:58,158 --> 00:26:59,785
Doctor, what happened?

350
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:02,996
Electrical energy, Miss Tyler.

351
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:07,876
Every atom in existence is
bound by an electrical field.

352
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:10,921
The Reality Bomb cancels it out.

353
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:13,090
Structure falls apart.

354
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:17,344
That test was focused
on the prisoners alone,

355
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:20,764
full transmission will dissolve

356
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:24,685
every form of matter.

357
00:27:25,394 --> 00:27:28,355
-The stars are going out.
-The 27 planets.

358
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:30,649
They become one vast transmitter.

359
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:36,238
-Blasting that wavelength...
-Across the entire universe.

360
00:27:36,822 --> 00:27:39,992
Never stopping, never faltering,
never fading.

361
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:44,496
People and planets and stars
will become dust,

362
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:50,002
and the dust will become atoms,
and the atoms will become nothing.

363
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:52,713
And the wavelength will continue

364
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:56,967
breaking through the rift
at the heart of the Medusa Cascade

365
00:27:57,092 --> 00:28:01,013
into every dimension, every parallel.

366
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:05,601
Every single corner of creation!

367
00:28:05,934 --> 00:28:10,147
This is my ultimate victory, Doctor!

368
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:16,111
The destruction of reality itself!

369
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:19,573
Prepare for universal detonation!

370
00:28:19,948 --> 00:28:22,618
The fleet will gather at the Crucible!

371
00:28:22,743 --> 00:28:27,122
All Daleks will return to shelter
from the cataclysm!

372
00:28:27,706 --> 00:28:32,461
We will become the only life forms
in existence!

373
00:28:33,003 --> 00:28:36,757
But they're leaving! Dad, they're going,
the Daleks are going.

374
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:38,634
Going where, though?

375
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:43,096
And Donna's still out there.
It's not over yet, sweetheart.

376
00:28:57,819 --> 00:29:01,240
Just my luck. I climb through
two miles of ventilation shafts

377
00:29:01,323 --> 00:29:05,077
chasing life signs on this thing,
and who do I find?

378
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,996
-Mickey Mouse.
-You can talk, Captain Cheesecake.

379
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:13,710
-Good to see you.
-And that's "beefcake".

380
00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:15,963
And that's enough hugging.

381
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:20,592
We meet at last, Miss Smith.

382
00:29:20,676 --> 00:29:22,678
There is something we can do.

383
00:29:22,803 --> 00:29:25,430
You've got to understand,
I have a son down there on Earth.

384
00:29:25,514 --> 00:29:27,849
He's only 14 years old.

385
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:30,269
I brought this.

386
00:29:31,311 --> 00:29:33,605
It was given to me by
a Verron soothsayer.

387
00:29:33,689 --> 00:29:37,859
He said, "This is for the end of days."

388
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:43,031
Is that a Warp Star?

389
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:45,158
Gonna tell me what a Warp Star is?

390
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:48,453
A warpfold conjugation
trapped in a carbonised shell.

391
00:29:48,537 --> 00:29:50,372
It's an explosion, Mickey.

392
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:53,500
An explosion waiting to happen.

393
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:58,046
This is Osterhagen Station Five.
Are you receiving, Station One?

394
00:29:58,171 --> 00:30:01,300
I've got you. That makes three
of us. And three is all we need.

395
00:30:01,383 --> 00:30:03,802
My name is Anna Zhou, what's yours?

396
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:07,306
Martha Jones. What about you,
Station Four? You never said.

397
00:30:07,389 --> 00:30:11,059
I don't want my name on this.
Given what we're about to do.

398
00:30:12,686 --> 00:30:15,856
So what happens now? Do we do it?

399
00:30:15,939 --> 00:30:17,149
No. Not yet.

400
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:20,652
UNIT instructions say once
three Osterhagen Stations are online...

401
00:30:20,736 --> 00:30:23,572
Yeah, well, I've got a higher authority,
way above UNIT.

402
00:30:23,697 --> 00:30:25,824
And there's one more thing
the Doctor would do.

403
00:30:26,241 --> 00:30:28,327
-So, what is this thing?
-It's our only hope.

404
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:30,579
A Z-Neutrino biological
inversion catalyser.

405
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:31,955
Yeah. Earth girl, remember?

406
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,749
Davros said he built those Daleks
out of himself.

407
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,751
His genetic code
runs through the entire race.

408
00:30:35,876 --> 00:30:38,003
If I can use this to lock
the Crucible's transmission

409
00:30:38,086 --> 00:30:40,589
-onto Davros himself...
-It destroys the Daleks!

410
00:30:40,714 --> 00:30:42,174
Biggest backfire in history!

411
00:30:42,257 --> 00:30:45,802
Incoming transmission!
Origin planet Earth.

412
00:30:46,053 --> 00:30:47,971
Display.

413
00:30:48,722 --> 00:30:52,225
This is Martha Jones representing
the Unified Intelligence Taskforce

414
00:30:52,309 --> 00:30:53,769
on behalf of the human race.

415
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:59,274
SUPREME DALEK: Send transmission
to the Vault. Continue to monitor.

416
00:30:59,399 --> 00:31:02,444
...for the Dalek Crucible.
Repeat, can you hear me?

417
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:03,695
Put me through.

418
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:07,074
It begins, as Dalek Caan foretold.

419
00:31:07,157 --> 00:31:10,494
DALEK CAAN: The children of time
will gather.

420
00:31:10,619 --> 00:31:12,996
And one of them will die!

421
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,582
Stop saying that! Put me through!

422
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:19,544
Doctor. I'm sorry, I had to.

423
00:31:19,628 --> 00:31:23,590
Oh, but the Doctor is powerless.
My prisoner.

424
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:25,509
State your intent.

425
00:31:25,634 --> 00:31:27,511
I've got the Osterhagen Key.

426
00:31:27,636 --> 00:31:31,223
Leave this planet and its people alone
or I'll use it.

427
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:33,558
Osterhagen what?
What's an Osterhagen Key?

428
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:37,771
There's a chain of 25 nuclear warheads
placed in strategic points

429
00:31:37,854 --> 00:31:40,190
beneath the Earth's crust.

430
00:31:40,315 --> 00:31:44,528
If I use the key, they detonate
and the Earth gets ripped apart.

431
00:31:44,611 --> 00:31:46,738
What? Who invented that?

432
00:31:46,822 --> 00:31:50,242
Well, someone called Osterhagen,
I suppose. Martha, are you insane?

433
00:31:50,492 --> 00:31:53,161
The Osterhagen Key is to be used

434
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:56,748
if the suffering of the human race
is so great,

435
00:31:56,832 --> 00:31:58,792
so without hope,

436
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:01,545
that this becomes the final option.

437
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,422
That's never an option!

438
00:32:03,505 --> 00:32:06,633
Don't argue with me, Doctor!
'Cause it's more than that.

439
00:32:06,716 --> 00:32:09,678
Now, I reckon the Daleks need
these 27 planets for something,

440
00:32:09,803 --> 00:32:13,265
but what if it becomes 267
What happens then?

441
00:32:13,348 --> 00:32:15,559
Daleks? Would you risk it?

442
00:32:15,851 --> 00:32:17,436
She's good.

443
00:32:17,519 --> 00:32:21,231
-MARTHA: Who's that?
-My name's Rose. Rose Tyler.

444
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:25,694
Oh, my God. He found you.

445
00:32:28,029 --> 00:32:30,657
Second transmission, internal!

446
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:32,117
Display.

447
00:32:32,325 --> 00:32:36,288
Captain Jack Harkness
calling all Dalek boys and girls.

448
00:32:36,371 --> 00:32:38,874
Are you receiving me?

449
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:42,252
Don't send in your goons
or I'll set this thing off!

450
00:32:42,544 --> 00:32:44,296
He's still alive!

451
00:32:45,005 --> 00:32:46,965
Oh, my God, that's my mum!

452
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:48,800
DOCTOR: Mickey, Captain,
what are you doing?

453
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:51,178
I've got a Warp Star wired
into the mainframe.

454
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:54,890
I break this shell,
the entire Crucible goes up.

455
00:32:55,015 --> 00:32:57,142
You can't!
Where did you get a Warp Star?

456
00:32:57,225 --> 00:33:00,729
From me. We had no choice.
We saw what happened to the prisoners.

457
00:33:00,896 --> 00:33:02,772
Impossible.

458
00:33:03,398 --> 00:33:07,819
That face. After all these years.

459
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:09,571
Davros.

460
00:33:10,739 --> 00:33:15,410
It's been quite a while.
Sarah Jane Smith, remember?

461
00:33:15,535 --> 00:33:18,747
Oh, this is meant to be!

462
00:33:18,872 --> 00:33:21,124
The circle of time is closing.

463
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:26,588
You were there on Skaro
at the very beginning of my creation.

464
00:33:26,922 --> 00:33:28,840
And I've learnt how to fight since then.

465
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:31,760
You let the Doctor go
or this Warp Star, it gets opened.

466
00:33:31,885 --> 00:33:34,221
I'll do it. Don't imagine I wouldn't.

467
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:36,598
Now that's what I call a ransom!

468
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:40,352
Doctor?

469
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:43,772
And the prophecy unfolds.

470
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:46,483
DALEK CAAN:
The Doctor's soul is revealed!

471
00:33:46,608 --> 00:33:48,109
(EVIL LAUGH)

472
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:51,780
See him! See the heart of him!

473
00:33:52,531 --> 00:33:55,951
The man who abhors violence.

474
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,911
Never carrying a gun.

475
00:33:58,036 --> 00:34:00,372
But this is the truth, Doctor!

476
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:04,960
You take ordinary people and
you fashion them into weapons.

477
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:10,924
Behold your children of time
transformed into murderers.

478
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:14,553
I made the Daleks, Doctor.
You made this.

479
00:34:14,636 --> 00:34:15,971
They're trying to help.

480
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:19,724
Already I have seen them
sacrificed today

481
00:34:19,808 --> 00:34:22,060
for their beloved Doctor.

482
00:34:23,228 --> 00:34:27,065
The Earth woman who fell
opening the Subwave Network.

483
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:29,192
-Who was that?
-Harriet Jones.

484
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,280
She gave her life to get you here.

485
00:34:37,993 --> 00:34:40,078
How many more? Just think.

486
00:34:40,161 --> 00:34:43,999
How many have died in your name?

487
00:35:10,734 --> 00:35:14,529
The Doctor. The man who keeps running,

488
00:35:14,613 --> 00:35:18,533
never looking back
because he dare not out of shame.

489
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:22,370
This is my final victory, Doctor.

490
00:35:22,787 --> 00:35:25,874
I have shown you yourself.

491
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:31,046
Enough.

492
00:35:31,129 --> 00:35:34,007
Engage defence zero five.

493
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:36,593
It's the Crucible or the Earth.

494
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:39,137
Transmat engaged!

495
00:35:45,018 --> 00:35:47,604
-JACK: I've got you.
-Don't move, all of you. Stay still!

496
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:52,233
Guard them! On your knees,
all of you! Surrender!

497
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,319
Do as he says.

498
00:36:00,075 --> 00:36:01,743
Mum. I told you not to.

499
00:36:01,868 --> 00:36:04,245
Yeah, well, I couldn't leave you.

500
00:36:05,705 --> 00:36:09,000
The final prophecy is in place.

501
00:36:09,084 --> 00:36:13,755
The Doctor and his children
all gathered as witnesses!

502
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:20,136
Supreme Dalek, the time has come. Now!

503
00:36:21,554 --> 00:36:24,557
Detonate the Reality Bomb!

504
00:36:33,942 --> 00:36:37,070
Activate planetary alignment field.

505
00:36:42,701 --> 00:36:47,914
Universal Reality Detonation
in 200 rels.

506
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:52,293
You can't, Davros, just listen to me!
Just stop!

507
00:36:58,591 --> 00:37:00,260
(LAUGHING)

508
00:37:00,969 --> 00:37:04,139
Nothing can stop the detonation!

509
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:07,934
Nothing and no one!

510
00:37:08,643 --> 00:37:10,562
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

511
00:37:11,146 --> 00:37:14,107
Ready! Maximum power!

512
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:24,409
But that's...

513
00:37:26,494 --> 00:37:28,371
(WHOOSHING)

514
00:37:28,455 --> 00:37:29,831
Impossible!

515
00:37:38,339 --> 00:37:39,799
Brilliant!

516
00:37:48,892 --> 00:37:50,101
Don't!

517
00:38:00,528 --> 00:38:02,614
Activate holding cell.

518
00:38:04,365 --> 00:38:05,784
Doctor!

519
00:38:08,369 --> 00:38:09,954
I've got it!

520
00:38:10,371 --> 00:38:12,207
But I don't know what to do!

521
00:38:14,834 --> 00:38:16,211
Donna!

522
00:38:18,546 --> 00:38:20,298
Donna! Are you all right, Donna?

523
00:38:20,423 --> 00:38:22,217
DAVROS: Destroy the weapon.

524
00:38:24,177 --> 00:38:27,555
I was wrong about your warriors, Doctor.

525
00:38:28,056 --> 00:38:29,974
They are pathetic!

526
00:38:30,892 --> 00:38:34,354
-How come there's two of you?
-Human biological met a crisis.

527
00:38:34,437 --> 00:38:36,815
Never mind that. Now we've got
no way of stopping the Reality Bomb.

528
00:38:36,898 --> 00:38:41,027
Detonation in 20 rels. Nineteen...

529
00:38:41,110 --> 00:38:45,073
Stand witness, Time Lord.
Stand witness, humans.

530
00:38:45,198 --> 00:38:48,159
Your strategies have failed.

531
00:38:48,243 --> 00:38:50,829
Your weapons are useless.

532
00:38:50,912 --> 00:38:54,666
And, oh,
the end of the universe has come!

533
00:38:54,874 --> 00:38:58,837
SUPREME DALEK: ...nine, eight, seven,

534
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:01,673
six, five four,

535
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:05,760
three, two, one.

536
00:39:07,595 --> 00:39:09,722
(BEEPING)

537
00:39:12,058 --> 00:39:14,561
And closing all Z-Neutrino relay loops

538
00:39:14,644 --> 00:39:18,439
using an internalised synchronous
back-feed reversal loop.

539
00:39:18,565 --> 00:39:20,358
That button there.

540
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:25,697
-System in shutdown!
-Detonation negative! Explain!

541
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:28,950
Explain! Explain!

542
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:32,287
-Donna, you can't even change a plug!
-Do you wanna bet, Time Boy?

543
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:34,831
You'll suffer for this!

544
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:36,499
(SCREAMING)

545
00:39:37,709 --> 00:39:41,671
Ooh, bio-electric dampening field
with a retrogressive arc inversion.

546
00:39:41,754 --> 00:39:43,631
Exterminate her!

547
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:48,094
Exterminate! Exterminate!

548
00:39:48,177 --> 00:39:49,637
Exterminate!

549
00:39:56,394 --> 00:39:58,897
Weapons non-functional!

550
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:02,734
Whor! Macrotransmission of a K-filter
wavelength blocking Dalek weaponry

551
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:04,652
in a self-replicating
energy blindfold matrix.

552
00:40:04,777 --> 00:40:06,404
How did you work that out? You're...

553
00:40:06,487 --> 00:40:09,365
Time Lord, part Time Lord.

554
00:40:09,449 --> 00:40:11,534
Part human! Oh, yes!

555
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:13,786
That was a two-way
biological met a crisis.

556
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:17,999
Half Doctor, half Donna.

557
00:40:18,166 --> 00:40:19,709
Doctor Donna.

558
00:40:21,002 --> 00:40:23,838
Just like the Ood said, remember?
They saw it coming!

559
00:40:23,922 --> 00:40:25,965
The Doctor Donna!

560
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:29,719
Holding cells deactivated.
Unseal the Vault.

561
00:40:30,053 --> 00:40:33,348
Well, don't just stand there,
you skinny boys in suits!

562
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:35,183
Get to work!

563
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:39,145
Stop them!
Get her away from the controls.

564
00:40:39,228 --> 00:40:41,272
And spin.

565
00:40:41,731 --> 00:40:44,025
Help me! Help me!

566
00:40:45,318 --> 00:40:47,153
DONNA: And the other way.

567
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,784
-What did you do?
-A trip stitch circuit breaker

568
00:40:52,867 --> 00:40:54,702
in the psycho-kinetic
threshold manipulator!

569
00:40:54,786 --> 00:40:57,038
-But that's brilliant!
-Why did we never think of that?

570
00:40:57,121 --> 00:41:00,708
Because you two were
just Time Lords, you dumbos!

571
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:03,211
Lacking that little
bit of human, that gut instinct,

572
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:04,963
that comes hand in hand
with planet Earth.

573
00:41:05,046 --> 00:41:07,507
I can think of ideas you two
wouldn't dream of in a million years!

574
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:10,093
Oh, the universe
has been waiting for me!

575
00:41:10,176 --> 00:41:13,054
Now, let's send that trip stitch
all over the ship!

576
00:41:14,764 --> 00:41:19,060
Did I ever tell you? Best temp in
Chiswick, 100 words per minute!

577
00:41:19,143 --> 00:41:20,228
Ha!

578
00:41:21,562 --> 00:41:24,023
System malfunctioning!

579
00:41:24,107 --> 00:41:25,984
Motor casing interference!

580
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:30,154
What is happening? Explain!

581
00:41:33,741 --> 00:41:36,869
Come on then, boys,
we've got 27 planets to send home.

582
00:41:36,953 --> 00:41:38,121
Activate Magnatron!

583
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:40,581
Stop this at once!

584
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:42,709
Mickey!

585
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:45,378
You will desist!

586
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:48,673
Just stay where you are, mister.

587
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:50,925
Out of the way!

588
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:56,431
-Good to see you again!
-Yeah, you, too!

589
00:42:03,104 --> 00:42:06,107
Ready? And reverse!

590
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,614
Off you go, Clom.

591
00:42:13,698 --> 00:42:15,700
Back home, Adipose III!

592
00:42:15,783 --> 00:42:21,039
Shallacatop, Pyrovillia
and the Lost Moon of Poosh, sorted! Ha!

593
00:42:21,914 --> 00:42:23,124
Ha!

594
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:24,876
DOCTOR: We need more power.

595
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:26,961
Is anyone gonna tell us what's going on?

596
00:42:27,128 --> 00:42:30,131
He poured all his regeneration energy
into his spare hand.

597
00:42:30,214 --> 00:42:33,134
I touched the hand, he grew out of that
but that fed back into me.

598
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:36,345
But it just stayed dormant
in my head till the synapses

599
00:42:36,429 --> 00:42:38,222
got that extra little spark,
kicking them into life.

600
00:42:38,306 --> 00:42:39,849
Thank you, Davros!

601
00:42:44,687 --> 00:42:47,065
Part human, part Time Lord.

602
00:42:47,857 --> 00:42:50,193
And I got the best bit of the Doctor.

603
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,695
I got his mind.

604
00:42:52,779 --> 00:42:55,198
-SARAH JANE: So there's three of you?
-Three Doctors?

605
00:42:55,281 --> 00:42:57,408
I can't tell you
what I'm thinking right now.

606
00:42:57,492 --> 00:43:00,244
You are so unique,
the time lines were converging on you.

607
00:43:00,328 --> 00:43:01,746
A human being with a Time Lord brain!

608
00:43:01,871 --> 00:43:05,500
But you promised me, Dalek Caan!

609
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:08,086
Why did you not foresee this?

610
00:43:08,211 --> 00:43:10,505
(LAUGHING)

611
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:15,551
Oh, I think he did. Something's been
manipulating the time lines for ages.

612
00:43:15,635 --> 00:43:18,262
Getting Donna Noble to
the right place at the right time.

613
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:20,848
This would always have happened.

614
00:43:20,973 --> 00:43:23,893
I only helped, Doctor.

615
00:43:23,976 --> 00:43:27,313
You betrayed the Daleks!

616
00:43:27,396 --> 00:43:30,274
I saw the Daleks,

617
00:43:30,358 --> 00:43:33,236
what we have done
throughout time and space.

618
00:43:33,319 --> 00:43:36,197
I saw the truth of us, Creator,

619
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:39,534
and I decreed no more!

620
00:43:39,951 --> 00:43:43,037
I will descend to the Vault!

621
00:43:44,372 --> 00:43:45,456
Heads up!

622
00:43:45,540 --> 00:43:48,584
Davros, you have betrayed us!

623
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:50,419
It was Dalek Caan!

624
00:43:50,503 --> 00:43:55,216
The Vault will be purged!
You will all be exterminated!

625
00:43:58,845 --> 00:44:01,222
Like I was saying. Feel this!

626
00:44:05,935 --> 00:44:09,272
Oh, we've lost the Magnatron!
And there's only one planet left.

627
00:44:10,523 --> 00:44:12,900
Guess which one?
But we can use the Tardis.

628
00:44:16,279 --> 00:44:19,323
Holding Earth stability,
maintaining atmospheric shell.

629
00:44:19,407 --> 00:44:23,828
-The prophecy must complete.
-Don't listen to him!

630
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:27,748
I have seen the end of everything Dalek

631
00:44:27,874 --> 00:44:31,252
and you must make it happen, Doctor.

632
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,838
He's right. 'Cause with
or without a Reality Bomb,

633
00:44:33,921 --> 00:44:37,091
this Dalek Empire's big enough
to slaughter the cosmos.

634
00:44:38,092 --> 00:44:41,387
-They've got to be stopped.
-Just wait for the Doctor.

635
00:44:41,470 --> 00:44:42,680
I am the Doctor!

636
00:44:42,763 --> 00:44:46,684
Maximising Dalekenium power feeds.
Blasting them back!

637
00:44:46,767 --> 00:44:47,935
(EXPLOSION)

638
00:45:05,411 --> 00:45:08,122
-What have you done?
-Fulfilling the prophecy.

639
00:45:21,302 --> 00:45:23,054
There goes the time lock.

640
00:45:28,643 --> 00:45:31,687
Do you know what you've done?
Now, get in the Tardis!

641
00:45:33,481 --> 00:45:34,815
Everyone!

642
00:45:35,816 --> 00:45:38,152
All of you inside! Run!
In! In! In! In! In!

643
00:45:38,277 --> 00:45:42,865
Sarah Jane! Rose! Jackie! Jack! Mickey!

644
00:45:50,831 --> 00:45:55,169
Davros, come with me!
I promise I can save you.

645
00:45:55,294 --> 00:45:58,881
Never forget, Doctor, you did this!

646
00:45:59,382 --> 00:46:02,510
I name you forever!

647
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:07,431
You are the Destroyer of Worlds!

648
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:09,725
(SCREAMING)

649
00:46:11,352 --> 00:46:14,563
One will still die.

650
00:46:18,609 --> 00:46:21,612
And off we go!

651
00:46:33,874 --> 00:46:36,168
But what about the Earth?
It's stuck in the wrong part of space.

652
00:46:36,252 --> 00:46:39,213
I'm on it! Torchwood Hub, this is
the Doctor. Are you receiving me?

653
00:46:39,338 --> 00:46:40,381
Loud and clear.

654
00:46:40,464 --> 00:46:43,009
-Is Jack there?
-Can't get rid of him.

655
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:45,678
-Jack, what's her name?
-Gwen Cooper.

656
00:46:46,053 --> 00:46:49,890
Tell me, Gwen Cooper,
are you from an old Cardiff family?

657
00:46:49,974 --> 00:46:52,310
Yes, all the way back to the 1800s.

658
00:46:52,393 --> 00:46:55,313
Ah, thought so.
Spatial genetic multiplicity.

659
00:46:55,396 --> 00:46:56,856
Ah, yeah, it's a funny old world.

660
00:46:56,981 --> 00:46:59,191
Now, Torchwood, I want you to open up
that Rift Manipulator

661
00:46:59,275 --> 00:47:01,944
-and send all the power to me.
-Doing it now, sir.

662
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:03,863
-What's that for?
-It's a tow rope.

663
00:47:03,946 --> 00:47:06,532
-Sarah, what was your son's name?
-Luke! He's called Luke!

664
00:47:06,615 --> 00:47:09,410
-And the computer's called Mr Smith.
-Calling Luke and Mr Smith.

665
00:47:09,493 --> 00:47:12,204
This is the Doctor.
Come on, Luke, shake a leg.

666
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:15,666
-Is Mum there?
-Oh, she's fine and dandy.

667
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:17,668
Now, Mr Smith, I want you
to harness the rift power

668
00:47:17,752 --> 00:47:19,587
and loop it around the Tardis,
you got that?

669
00:47:19,712 --> 00:47:23,841
MR SMITH: I regret, I will need remote
access to Tardis base code numerals.

670
00:47:23,924 --> 00:47:25,718
Oh, blimey, that's gonna take a while.

671
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:28,763
SARAH JANE: No, no, no, let me!

672
00:47:29,013 --> 00:47:30,639
K9, out you come.

673
00:47:30,765 --> 00:47:32,683
K9: Affirmative, mistress.

674
00:47:32,767 --> 00:47:36,729
Oh, good dog!
K9, give Mr Smith the base code.

675
00:47:36,854 --> 00:47:40,274
Master. Tardis base code
now being transferred.

676
00:47:41,567 --> 00:47:43,361
K9: The process is simple.

677
00:47:43,444 --> 00:47:47,948
Now then, you lot. Sarah,
hold that down, Mickey, you hold that.

678
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:50,451
Do you know why this Tardis
is always rattling about the place?

679
00:47:50,534 --> 00:47:52,078
Rose, that, there.

680
00:47:52,161 --> 00:47:54,413
It's designed to have six pilots
and I have to do it single-handed!

681
00:47:54,497 --> 00:47:56,082
Martha, keep that level.
But not any more.

682
00:47:56,165 --> 00:47:58,042
Jack, there you go, steady that.

683
00:47:58,125 --> 00:48:02,463
Now we can fly this thing...
No, Jackie, no, no, not you.

684
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:06,967
Don't touch anything, just stand back.
Like it's meant to be flown!

685
00:48:07,093 --> 00:48:10,346
We've got the Torchwood rift
looped around the Tardis by Mr Smith

686
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:13,724
and we're gonna
fly planet Earth back home!

687
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:16,977
Right, then! Off we go.

688
00:48:36,664 --> 00:48:39,041
(CHEERING)

689
00:48:40,501 --> 00:48:42,670
(WHOOPING)

690
00:49:27,882 --> 00:49:31,093
That's really good, Jack,
I think you're the best.

691
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:42,289
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

692
00:50:47,211 --> 00:50:51,298
You know, you act like
such a lonely man.

693
00:50:51,632 --> 00:50:55,261
But look at you.
You've got the biggest family on Earth!

694
00:51:01,100 --> 00:51:05,437
Gotta go! He's only 14.
It's a long story.

695
00:51:06,188 --> 00:51:08,232
And thank you!

696
00:51:13,612 --> 00:51:17,324
DONNA: Yeah, I'm fine.
Are you all right? Yeah, I know.

697
00:51:18,492 --> 00:51:21,453
I'm gonna miss you. More than anyone.

698
00:51:21,537 --> 00:51:25,082
What do you mean? The Doctor's going to
take us home, isn't he?

699
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:27,209
Well, that's the point.

700
00:51:30,713 --> 00:51:33,716
I told you. No teleport!

701
00:51:35,259 --> 00:51:38,804
And, Martha, get rid
of that Osterhagen thing, eh?

702
00:51:39,513 --> 00:51:42,766
-Save the world one more time.
-Consider it done.

703
00:51:49,231 --> 00:51:52,109
You know, I'm not sure
about UNIT these days.

704
00:51:52,192 --> 00:51:55,404
Maybe there's something else
you could be doing.

705
00:51:57,740 --> 00:51:59,617
Oi, where are you going?

706
00:51:59,700 --> 00:52:02,536
Well, I'm not stupid.
I can work out what happens next.

707
00:52:02,620 --> 00:52:04,246
And, hey, I had a good time
in that parallel world

708
00:52:04,330 --> 00:52:08,167
but my gran passed away,
nice and peaceful.

709
00:52:08,250 --> 00:52:10,377
She spent her last years
Living in a mansion.

710
00:52:10,461 --> 00:52:13,547
There's nothing there for me now,
certainly not Rose.

711
00:52:14,882 --> 00:52:16,925
What will you do?

712
00:52:17,051 --> 00:52:20,012
Anything. Brand new life.
Just you watch.

713
00:52:22,556 --> 00:52:25,851
See you, boss. Hey, you two!

714
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:29,521
JACK: Oh. I thought I'd got rid of you.

715
00:52:36,153 --> 00:52:38,155
Just time for one last trip.

716
00:52:41,033 --> 00:52:45,496
Darlig Ulv Stranden. Better known as...

717
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:03,764
Oh! Fat lot of good this is!

718
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:08,018
Back of beyond. Bloody Norway!
I'm going to have to phone your father.

719
00:53:08,102 --> 00:53:09,937
He's on the nursery run.

720
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:13,524
I was pregnant, do you remember?
Had a baby boy.

721
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:15,526
Ah, brilliant, what did you call him?

722
00:53:15,609 --> 00:53:16,902
Doctor.

723
00:53:18,362 --> 00:53:21,782
-Really?
-No, you plum. He's called Tony.

724
00:53:21,990 --> 00:53:24,868
Hold on.
This is the parallel universe, right?

725
00:53:24,952 --> 00:53:26,036
You're back home.

726
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:27,955
And the walls of the world
are closing again,

727
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:30,207
now that the Reality Bomb
never happened.

728
00:53:30,290 --> 00:53:34,503
It's dimensional retroclosure.
See, I really get that stuff now!

729
00:53:34,962 --> 00:53:37,131
No, but I spent all that time
trying to find you.

730
00:53:37,256 --> 00:53:40,551
-I'm not going back now.
-But you've got to.

731
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:44,847
'Cause we saved the universe,
but at a cost.

732
00:53:44,972 --> 00:53:46,974
And the cost is him.

733
00:53:47,558 --> 00:53:50,060
He destroyed the Daleks.
He committed genocide.

734
00:53:50,144 --> 00:53:51,729
He's too dangerous
to be left on his own.

735
00:53:51,812 --> 00:53:53,021
You made me.

736
00:53:53,147 --> 00:53:57,317
Exactly. You were born in battle.
Full of blood and anger and revenge.

737
00:53:59,778 --> 00:54:02,156
Remind you of someone?

738
00:54:04,074 --> 00:54:06,618
That's me when we first met.

739
00:54:09,663 --> 00:54:13,083
And you made me better.
Now you can do the same for him.

740
00:54:13,167 --> 00:54:14,668
But he's not you.

741
00:54:14,752 --> 00:54:17,755
He needs you. That's very me.

742
00:54:19,381 --> 00:54:21,091
But it's better than that, though.

743
00:54:21,175 --> 00:54:23,719
Don't you see what
he's trying to give you?

744
00:54:23,844 --> 00:54:26,013
Tell her, go on.

745
00:54:28,849 --> 00:54:30,768
I look like him, I think like him.

746
00:54:30,851 --> 00:54:33,979
Same memories, same thoughts,
same everything.

747
00:54:34,062 --> 00:54:35,856
Except I've only got one heart.

748
00:54:35,981 --> 00:54:38,692
-Which means?
-I'm part human.

749
00:54:40,652 --> 00:54:44,990
Specifically, the ageing part.
I'll grow old and never regenerate.

750
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:48,327
I've only got one life, Rose Tyler.

751
00:54:51,330 --> 00:54:53,999
I could spend it with you if you want.

752
00:54:55,334 --> 00:54:58,128
You'll grow old at the same time as me?

753
00:54:58,212 --> 00:54:59,671
Together.

754
00:55:05,761 --> 00:55:08,639
(HEART BEATING)

755
00:55:08,722 --> 00:55:10,724
(TARDIS HUMS)

756
00:55:13,852 --> 00:55:18,857
We got to go, this reality
is sealing itself off forever.

757
00:55:19,650 --> 00:55:22,903
But it's still not right,

758
00:55:23,028 --> 00:55:26,573
'cause the Doctor's still you.

759
00:55:26,657 --> 00:55:28,408
And I'm him.

760
00:55:28,492 --> 00:55:32,246
All right. Both of you, answer me this.

761
00:55:34,331 --> 00:55:38,085
When I last stood on this beach
on the worst day of my life,

762
00:55:38,961 --> 00:55:41,755
what was the last thing you said to me?

763
00:55:42,798 --> 00:55:44,383
Go on, say it.

764
00:55:45,634 --> 00:55:47,594
I said, "Rose Tyler."

765
00:55:49,096 --> 00:55:51,974
Yeah, and how was
that sentence gonna end?

766
00:55:53,475 --> 00:55:55,352
Does it need saying?

767
00:55:58,105 --> 00:55:59,940
And you, Doctor?

768
00:56:01,817 --> 00:56:04,444
What was the end of that sentence?

769
00:56:53,076 --> 00:56:55,162
I thought we could try
the planet Felspoon.

770
00:56:55,287 --> 00:56:57,581
Just 'cause what a good name, Felspoon.

771
00:56:57,664 --> 00:57:00,042
Apparently it's got mountains
that sway in the breeze.

772
00:57:00,167 --> 00:57:02,836
Mountains that move, can you imagine?

773
00:57:03,378 --> 00:57:04,755
And how do you know that?

774
00:57:04,838 --> 00:57:08,383
Because it's in your head.
And if it's in your head, it's in mine.

775
00:57:08,508 --> 00:57:11,929
-And how does that feel?
-Brilliant! Fantastic! Motto bene!

776
00:57:12,012 --> 00:57:14,264
Great big universe packed into my brain!

777
00:57:14,389 --> 00:57:15,849
You know you could fix
that chameleon circuit

778
00:57:15,933 --> 00:57:17,976
if you just tried hot binding
the fragment links and superseding

779
00:57:18,060 --> 00:57:23,899
the binary, binary, binary, binary,
binary, binary, binary, binary...

780
00:57:23,982 --> 00:57:25,943
(GASPS) I'm fine!

781
00:57:26,026 --> 00:57:28,862
Nah, never mind Felspoon. You know
who I'd like to meet? Charlie Chaplin.

782
00:57:28,946 --> 00:57:30,864
I bet he's great, Charlie Chaplin.
Shall we do that?

783
00:57:30,989 --> 00:57:33,116
Shall we go and see Charlie Chaplin?
Shall we? Charlie Chaplin?

784
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:34,326
Charlie Chester? Charlie Brown.

785
00:57:34,409 --> 00:57:37,204
No, he's fiction, friction, fixing,
mixing, Rickston, Brixton.

786
00:57:37,329 --> 00:57:39,164
(GASPS)

787
00:57:42,459 --> 00:57:44,044
Oh, my God.

788
00:57:44,878 --> 00:57:47,673
Do you know what's happening?

789
00:57:50,759 --> 00:57:52,260
Yeah.

790
00:57:52,386 --> 00:57:56,723
There's never been
a human Time Lord met a crisis before now.

791
00:57:57,224 --> 00:58:00,394
-And you know why?
-Because there can't be.

792
00:58:04,398 --> 00:58:06,441
I want to stay.

793
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:10,112
Look at me. Donna, look at me.

794
00:58:16,118 --> 00:58:20,414
I was gonna be with you. Forever.

795
00:58:21,206 --> 00:58:22,541
I know.

796
00:58:24,084 --> 00:58:26,169
Rest of my life.

797
00:58:26,795 --> 00:58:29,965
Travelling in the Tardis.

798
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:33,927
The Doctor Donna.

799
00:58:37,889 --> 00:58:43,103
Oh! Oh, but I can't go back.

800
00:58:45,313 --> 00:58:47,357
Don't make me go back.

801
00:58:47,441 --> 00:58:51,319
Doctor, please,
please don't make me go back.

802
00:58:51,611 --> 00:58:53,113
Donna.

803
00:58:55,407 --> 00:58:58,910
Oh, Donna Noble. I am so sorry.

804
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:03,331
But we had the best of times.

805
00:59:05,917 --> 00:59:07,669
The best.

806
00:59:12,716 --> 00:59:15,135
-Goodbye.
-No, no, no, please.

807
00:59:15,218 --> 00:59:17,471
Please! No, no, no!

808
00:59:24,936 --> 00:59:26,188
No!

809
00:59:34,738 --> 00:59:35,781
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

810
00:59:35,864 --> 00:59:38,450
That must be her! Donna!

811
00:59:42,746 --> 00:59:44,831
-Help me.
-Donna?

812
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:48,668
Donna.

813
00:59:58,470 --> 01:00:00,847
She took my mind into her own head.

814
01:00:00,972 --> 01:00:03,183
But that's a Time Lord consciousness.

815
01:00:03,308 --> 01:00:05,602
All that knowledge, it was killing her.

816
01:00:05,685 --> 01:00:07,562
But she'll get better now?

817
01:00:07,687 --> 01:00:10,023
I had to wipe her mind completely.

818
01:00:10,107 --> 01:00:12,442
Every trace of me or the Tardis,

819
01:00:12,526 --> 01:00:16,196
anything we did together,
anywhere we went, had to go.

820
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:19,533
-All those wonderful things she did.
-I know.

821
01:00:21,368 --> 01:00:24,037
But that version of Donna is dead.

822
01:00:25,205 --> 01:00:28,458
'Cause if she remembers,
just for a second, she'll burn up.

823
01:00:28,542 --> 01:00:30,794
You can never tell her.

824
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:34,548
You can't mention me, or any of it,

825
01:00:35,632 --> 01:00:39,511
-for the rest of her life.
-But the whole world's talking about it.

826
01:00:39,594 --> 01:00:41,721
We travelled across space.

827
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:44,724
It'll just be a story.

828
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:49,646
One of those Donna Noble stories
where she missed it all again.

829
01:00:49,729 --> 01:00:52,107
-But she was better with you.
-Don't say that.

830
01:00:52,232 --> 01:00:54,067
No, she was!

831
01:00:54,151 --> 01:00:57,362
I just want you to know
that there are worlds out there

832
01:00:58,071 --> 01:01:00,240
safe in the sky because of her.

833
01:01:01,741 --> 01:01:03,994
That there are people
living in the light

834
01:01:05,745 --> 01:01:07,581
and singing songs of Donna Noble

835
01:01:09,291 --> 01:01:11,960
a thousand million light years away.

836
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:16,840
They will never forget her,

837
01:01:19,092 --> 01:01:21,386
while she can never remember.

838
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:26,266
And for one moment,

839
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:31,021
one shining moment,

840
01:01:34,983 --> 01:01:38,653
she was the most important woman
in the whole wide universe.

841
01:01:38,778 --> 01:01:41,656
She still is. She's my daughter.

842
01:01:42,782 --> 01:01:45,285
Then maybe you should tell her that
once in a while.

843
01:01:45,368 --> 01:01:50,373
I was asleep! On my bed,
in my clothes like a flipping kid.

844
01:01:50,457 --> 01:01:52,959
What did you let me do that for?

845
01:01:53,084 --> 01:01:55,003
Don't mind me. Donna.

846
01:01:55,837 --> 01:01:58,715
-John Smith.
-Mr Smith was just leaving.

847
01:01:58,798 --> 01:02:00,258
My phone's gone mad! 32 texts!

848
01:02:00,342 --> 01:02:02,844
Veena's gone barmy.
She's saying "planets in the sky!"

849
01:02:02,969 --> 01:02:05,805
What have I missed now?
Nice to meet you.

850
01:02:08,099 --> 01:02:10,977
As I said, I think you should go.

851
01:02:18,818 --> 01:02:22,864
How thick do you think I am? Planets!
I'll tell you what that was, dumbo,

852
01:02:22,948 --> 01:02:24,991
that's those two-for-one lagers
you get down the offy

853
01:02:25,075 --> 01:02:28,536
"cause you fancy that little man
in there with the goatee!

854
01:02:28,620 --> 01:02:30,830
Yes, you do. I've seen you!

855
01:02:30,914 --> 01:02:33,166
Donna, I was just going.

856
01:02:33,250 --> 01:02:35,126
Yeah, see you.
I'll tell you what, though,

857
01:02:35,210 --> 01:02:36,628
you're wasting your time with that one,

858
01:02:36,711 --> 01:02:39,673
because Susie Mair, she went on
that dating site, and she saw him.

859
01:02:39,756 --> 01:02:45,512
No, no... Listen, this is important!
Susie Mair wouldn't lie!

860
01:02:46,012 --> 01:02:48,098
Not unless it was about calories!

861
01:02:49,015 --> 01:02:50,809
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

862
01:02:50,892 --> 01:02:54,187
Ah! You'll have quite a bit of this.

863
01:02:55,063 --> 01:02:57,232
Atmospheric disturbance.

864
01:02:57,357 --> 01:03:00,860
Still, it'll pass. Everything does.

865
01:03:04,739 --> 01:03:06,783
Bye then, Wilfred.

866
01:03:08,743 --> 01:03:11,246
Oh, and, Doctor.

867
01:03:11,371 --> 01:03:14,124
What about you now? Who have you got?

868
01:03:15,125 --> 01:03:18,336
I mean, all those friends of yours...

869
01:03:18,420 --> 01:03:21,047
They've all got someone else.

870
01:03:21,881 --> 01:03:25,343
Still, that's fine. I'm fine.

871
01:03:25,844 --> 01:03:27,220
I'll watch out for you, sir.

872
01:03:27,304 --> 01:03:30,432
-You can't ever tell her.
-No, no.

873
01:03:31,599 --> 01:03:34,060
But every night, Doctor,

874
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:38,898
when it gets dark
and the stars come out,

875
01:03:40,066 --> 01:03:41,735
I'll look up.

876
01:03:42,861 --> 01:03:46,906
On her behalf, I'll look up at the sky

877
01:03:48,825 --> 01:03:50,618
and think of you.

878
01:03:51,745 --> 01:03:53,288
Thank you.

